
---


@startuml

' Classes
class WebPortal {
  -version: String
  -url: String
}

class Building {
  -id: String
  -name: String
  -energyClass: String
  -address: String
  -yearOfConstruction: Integer
  -owner: User
  -entries: List<Entry>
  -images: List<Image>
  -profilePhoto: Image
}

class Entry {
  -name: String
  -isPublic: Boolean
  -content: String
  -unit: String
}

class TextualEntry <|-- Entry
class NumericEntry <|-- Entry

class Image {
  -fileName: String
}

class User {
  -username: String
  -email: String
  -password: String
  -buildings: List<Building>
  -comments: List<Comment>
}

class Comment {
  -content: String
  -user: User
  -building: Building
}

class Administrator <|-- User {
  -idCardNumber: String
}

class FullTextSearch {
  +search(query: String): List<Building>
}

' Relationships
WebPortal "1" --> "0..*" Building
User "1" --> "0..*" Building
Building "1" --> "0..*" Entry
Building "1" --> "0..*" Image
Entry "1" --> "0..1" TextualEntry
Entry "1" --> "0..1" NumericEntry
User "1" --> "0..*" Comment
Comment "1" --> "1" User
Comment "1" --> "1" Building
Administrator "1" --> "0..*" User

@enduml

---

### 📌 **Use Cases and Actors Mapping**

| Use Case                     | Actor         | Description |
|-----------------------------|---------------|-------------|
| Register as a User          | Visitor       | A visitor registers with a username, email, and password. |
| Confirm Email Address       | Visitor       | The user confirms their email by clicking a link sent during registration. |
| Activate User Account       | Administrator | An administrator activates the user’s account after registration. |
| Log In                      | User          | A registered user logs in with their credentials. |
| Create a Building           | User          | A user creates a new building with all required information. |
| Add Entry to a Building     | User          | A user adds an entry (text or number) to one of their buildings. |
| Set Entry as Public         | User          | A user makes an entry visible to all visitors. |
| Upload Image to Building    | User          | A user uploads images to a building and selects one as the profile photo. |
| Comment on a Building       | User          | A user can comment on another user's building. |
| Delete Comment              | Administrator | An administrator deletes inappropriate comments from the system. |

---

### 🔄 **Relationships Between Use Cases**

- **Register as a User → Confirm Email Address**: Confirmation is a prerequisite for activation.
- **Register as a User → Activate User Account**: Admin must activate the user before login.
- **Activate User Account → Log In**: Only activated users can log in.
- **Log In → Create a Building**: Users need to be logged in to create a building.
- **Log In → Add Entry to a Building**: Users need to be logged in to add entries.
- **Log In → Upload Image to Building**: Users need to be logged in to upload images.
- **Log In → Comment on a Building**: Users must be logged in to comment.
- **Delete Comment ← Comment on a Building**: Administrators delete comments that were posted by others.
- **Full Text Search ← All Use Cases**: Visitors can always perform a full-text search for buildings.

